3. NFT contract for energy + bandwidth

We’ll use ERC721Enumerable so we can list tokens by owner easily.   

3.1. Solidity contract (EnergyRigNFT.sol)

`solidity
// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
pragma solidity ^0.8.20;

import "@openzeppelin/contracts/token/ERC721/extensions/ERC721Enumerable.sol";
import "@openzeppelin/contracts/access/Ownable.sol";

contract EnergyRigNFT is ERC721Enumerable, Ownable {
    uint256 public nextTokenId = 1;

    constructor() ERC721("EnergyRig", "ERIG") {}

    function mint(address to) external onlyOwner {
        _safeMint(to, nextTokenId);
        nextTokenId++;
    }
}
`

This gives you:

- balanceOf(owner)  
- tokenOfOwnerByIndex(owner, index)  
- totalSupply()  

Perfect for listing NFTs per wallet.   

