4. NFT metadata with picture + resource attributes

Each NFT will point to a JSON file (off‑chain) with:

- Image URL (your “picture”)  
- Attributes: kWh, bandwidth, capsule MB, etc.

Example metadata.json:

`json
{
  "name": "Rig Energy Pass #1",
  "description": "Grants energy and bandwidth from Manierism Rig.",
  "image": "https://your-cdn.com/images/rigpass1.png",
  "attributes": [
    { "trait_type": "kwh", "value": 100 },
    { "traittype": "bandwidthmb", "value": 5000 },
    { "traittype": "capsulemb", "value": 2000 }
  ]
}
`

You upload this to IPFS or any static host, then set tokenURI(tokenId) in your contract (you can extend the contract later to support that).

From Python, you’ll:

1. Call tokenURI(tokenId)  
2. GET the JSON  
3. Read image + attributes  
4. Use that to update rig balances and print a “card” in the terminal.   

